        <span class="current">301 Redirect</span>
      </div>
      <h1>301 Redirect</h1>
      <p class="definition"><strong>301 Redirect</strong> is a server-side HTTP status code that permanently sends visitors and search engines from an old URL to a new one — passing nearly all SEO authority for site owners moving, merging, or renaming pages.</p>
      <div class="term-meta">
        <span class="term-meta-item">Category: <strong style="color: var(--brand);">Technical SEO</strong></span>
        <span class="term-meta-dot"></span>
        <span class="term-meta-item">Difficulty: Beginner</span>
        <span class="term-meta-dot"></span>
